div1.p: TERRITORY OF WASHINGTON, County of Spokane } SS.

Territory of Washington
Plaintiff
vs.
S.P. White
Defendant }
In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the First Fourth Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Cheney, Spokane County, in said Territory
To the Sheriff of Lincoln County, Greeting:

IN THE NAME OF THE UNITED STATES, You are hereby commanded to summon W. G. Ring to be and appear before the District Court aforesaid at the Court House, in Cheney, in said County, on the forthwith day of A.D. 1885, at o'clock, M. to there give evidence in the above entitiled cause on the part of said Defendant S.P. White
Witness the Hon. George Turner Associate Judge of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal thereof affixed, this 17 day of April A.D. 1885

Kate W. Feuerbach Clerk.
By R. Strobach Deputy.

TERRITORY OF WASHINGTON,
County of Spokane Lincoln } SS.
I hereby certify that I served the within Subpoena on the within named witness by reading the same to in said County, on this day of A.D. 188
I hereby certify that I made diligent search for the within named W. G. Ring and failed to find him in any county

John Cody,
Sheriff
Lincoln County
by J.M. Friedlander Dep.
In the District Court of the Territory of Washington, and for the First Judicial District thereof, holding Terms at Cheney, Spokane County, in said Territory
